{"ticker": "JBL", "company": "JABIL INC", "weight_sum": 0.14, "etfs": ["PRNT"], "is_private": false, "query": "($JBL OR \"Jabil\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since_time:1777740043 until_time:1777748312", "n_fetched": 2, "n_kept": 1, "n_dropped": 1, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2050628704653689258", "url": "https://x.com/athuinvests/status/2050628704653689258", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/athuinvests/status/2050628704653689258", "text": "Looked into the $SIVE \u2192 Ayar Labs \u2192 Cerebras \u2192 OpenAI mapping (via Jabil or Ayar Labs).\n\nCerebras chose Ranovus (not Ayar Labs or Jabil) for its CPO program. They\u2019re integrating its Odin Platform optical engine directly into the Cerebras Wafer-Scale Engine (WSE) - widely considered the world\u2019s largest and fastest AI processor.\n\nOpenAI, G42, AWS, and Meta are all publicly collaborating with Cerebras to integrate or use its chips (OpenAI\u2019s deal alone is >$10B).\n\nWhy no confirmed link yet:\n\n1. The Odin Platform uses a completely different laser technology than Sivers - proprietary Multi-Wavelength Quantum Dot Lasers (QDL) instead of Sivers\u2019 InP CW DFB laser arrays. That pretty much settles the direct link for now.\n\n2. There is no confirmed use of Ayar Labs\u2019 TeraPHY engine with Cerebras. The only connection so far is a joint industry panel in April 2025 where execs from Ayar Labs, Cerebras, AMD, and Microsoft Azure discussed CPO and photonics in general.\n\n3. Jabil acts purely as a fabricator/assembler for these optical solutions, not as a component supplier.\n\nThe possibility ahead:\n\nThe only realistic path right now for Sivers lasers to reach Cerebras would be through a future Ayar Labs \u00d7 Cerebras collaboration. \n\nAs Ayar Labs scales its TeraPHY production and customer wins, we could have a meaningful partnership between both the companies. April 2025 industry panel shows that could be a real possibility. \n\nCerebras could opens its supply chain in the future to multiple players. Ranovus & Ayar Labs. The fact that both companies use different laser tech actually increases the chance they could both be used, depending on customer preference and specific use case.\n\nThe other possibility is if Ranovus collaborates with SIVE for its future photonic engines using InP CW DFB laser arrays, which is a much lower probable.\n\nBottom link: This could open a massive new supply chain door for $SIVE. Ayar Labs x Cerebras partnership is the most likely path toward that happening.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 3, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 14, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 1645, "createdAt": "Sat May 02 17:29:16 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 7, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2050628704653689258", "displayTextRange": [0, 271], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "athuinvests", "url": "https://x.com/athuinvests", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/athuinvests", "id": "1869731425471152128", "name": "Athu Invests", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2036181254115303425/gXd64OKj_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1869731425471152128/1777139286", "description": "", "location": "", "followers": 1014, "following": 103, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Thu Dec 19 13:08:17 +0000 2024", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 1802, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 132, "statusesCount": 1060, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2048245432078241806"], "profile_bio": {"description": "Future Tech & Growth Industry Investment Research.\n\nAI/Software Developer.\n\n\"Where capital flows, opportunity follows.\"", "entities": {"des